'Tirana' (Standard ; regional Gheg Albanian: Tirona) is the capital and the
largest city of Albania. Modern Tirana was founded as an Ottoman town in 1614 by
Sulejman Bargjini, a local ruler from Mullet. Tirana became Albaniaâs capital
city in 1920 and has a population of 400,000, with metro area population of
763,634. The city is host to public institutions and private universities, and
is the centre of the political, economical, and cultural life of the country.
